  "optimization_hints": [
    "Q1: Parallel full scan + SIMD aggregation on 60M-row lineitem. High-selectivity date filter (98%) → early materialization acceptable. Use vectorized hash aggregation (4 groups) with partial pre-aggregation per thread.",
    "Q3: High-cardinality GROUP BY (2.5M groups) + 3-way join (customer→orders→lineitem). Use hash join: build on customer (filtered 1.5M→300K), probe orders (filtered 15M→7.2M), then probe lineitem (60M→30M). Parallel morsel-driven execution. Top-K sort elimination (LIMIT 10).",
    "Q6: Single-table scan with selective compound filter (0.02 selectivity). Non-vectorizable discount predicate due to expression complexity. Parallel scan with early predicate pushdown; use SIMD for date/quantity range checks. Result is ~1.2M rows → final aggregate fits in memory."
  ],
  "summary": "TPC-H workload dominated by large-table fact scans: lineitem (60M rows, 3 queries), orders (15M rows, 1 query), customer (1.5M rows, 1 query). Q1 is a simple high-selectivity aggregate (4 groups); Q6 is selective scan+agg; Q3 is the bottleneck—3-way join with 2.5M-group output and top-10 sort. Hardware: 64 cores + AVX-512 + HDD enables massive parallelism via thread-parallel morsel-driven execution. Key optimizations: parallel scan+filter+partial agg for Q1/Q6, join reordering + hash-join + early filtering for Q3, and vectorized operators throughout."
